ed to practice a lot=\r\n before that knowledge becomes \n&gt; natural and permanent and you stop gettin=\r\ng startled.\n&gt; \n&gt; Similarly, actionss without knowledge are useless too. One=\r\n keeps \n&gt; performing actions forever then. One watching a movie 1000 times =\r\nwithout \n&gt; the knowledge that it is unreal and should not be taken seriousl=\r\ny will \n&gt; get startled each time and enjoy the experience.\n&gt; \n&gt; In http://t=\r\ninyurl.com/homamwhy document (from WAVES 2010 conference), I \n&gt; gave an ana=\r\nlogy. Suppose one needs to walk to the top of a mountain. One \n&gt; with gyaan=\r\na but no karma is like a person standing at the base and \n&gt; staring at the =\r\npinnacle. He knows where to go, but he will remain at the \n&gt; base forever. =\r\nOne with karma but no gyaana is like a person going around \n&gt; the mountain =\r\nforever. One balancing karma and gyana, i.e. engaging in \n&gt; actions cocuple=\r\nd with the correct understanding that all is Brahman, is \n&gt; like a person c=\r\nlimbing the mountain and watching the top from time to \n&gt; time to correct o=\r\nne&#39;s course. He will eventually reach the pinnacle. \n&gt; Karma and gyaana nee=\r\nd to go hand in hand and are definitely not \n&gt; opposites or alternatives.\n&gt;=\r\n \n&gt; &gt; is free from all the faults of samsaraf samsara, one does not find an=\r\ny \n&gt; &gt; benefit out\n&gt; &gt; of actions which he has done or which he has to do.\n=\r\n&gt; \n&gt; Actions with attachment (i.e. actions with agyaana) can be criticized =\r\n\n&gt; and dismissed. But detached actions (i.e. actions with gyaana) should be=\r\n \n&gt; encouraged.\n&gt; \n&gt; *        *        *\n&gt; \n&gt; This equating of liberation a=\r\nnd spiritual progress with akarma \n&gt; (inaction), instead of detached action=\r\n (nishkaama karma), is what led to \n&gt; the temporary downfall of Sanatana Dh=\r\narma in the world. This is \n&gt; pseudo-Vedanta and not the real deal.\n&gt; \n&gt; As=\r\n long as you self-identify with a body, desires arise from time to \n&gt; time.=\r\n The purer your conditioning is, the more dharmik those desires \n&gt; will be.=\r\n Perform the best action within your capability to fulfil those \n&gt; desires.=\r\n Once action is done, surrender it to the Lord and do not think \n&gt; about it=\r\n anymore. Whatever result comes, take it as God&#39;s will and do \n&gt; not regret=\r\n or rejoice. No pride and no shame. As you do this more and \n&gt; more, your c=\r\nonditioning will drop more and more and your consciousness \n&gt; will become p=\r\nurer and purer. Your conscience will speak louder and \n&gt; louder and your se=\r\nnse of dharma will be refined. Your desires will \n&gt; become more and more dh=\r\narmik. You will transition from fulfilling dharma \n&gt; towards individual sel=\r\nf to fulfilling dharma towards universal self. \n&gt; Eventually, you will reac=\r\nh a stage where you perform actions with no \n&gt; identification. Then action =\r\nbecome non-action.\n&gt; \n&gt; Vishnu, Shiva, rishis etc also do not engage in ina=\r\nction. Instead, they \n&gt; engage in detached action for maintaining and suppo=\r\nrting the Cosmic \n&gt; Order, as determined by the Supreme Cosmic Being and Hi=\r\ns Shakti (his \n&gt; Kinetic aspect).\n&gt; \n&gt; *        *        *\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; One acts =\r\nonly when there is desire. A desireless man, whose desires \n&gt; &gt; have been\n&gt;=\r\n &gt; fulfilled, who has risen above desires, whose desire is the atman, has \n=\r\n&gt; &gt; no\n&gt; &gt; necessity to act.\n&gt; \n&gt; First of all, everybody whose self-identi=\r\nfication with a body remains \n&gt; atleast to a small extent IS performing act=\r\nions continually. At the bare \n&gt; minimum, one performs actions like breathi=\r\nng, eating, drinking water, \n&gt; urinating and defecating, which affect the l=\r\nives of millions of \n&gt; micro-organisms.\n&gt; \n&gt; Second, one &quot;whose de