a and \n&gt; it will just happen. Or perhaps you will become r=\r\nealized even without \n&gt; sannyasa. In either case, the end goal is internal =\r\ndetachment and \n&gt; self-realization and not external renunciation.\n&gt; \n&gt; Anyb=\r\nody who tells you that a *specific* external action or object is a \n&gt; *must=\r\n* for internal purification and liberation is over-selling it.\n&gt; \n&gt; *      =\r\n  *        *\n&gt; \n&gt; &gt; Without abandonment of the concerns of worldly life, kn=\r\nowledge cannot \n&gt; &gt; be pursued\n&gt; &gt; with unabated vigor and devotion. It doe=\r\ns not mean that the sannyasin \n&gt; &gt; undervalues\n&gt; &gt; human society and discar=\r\nds all men without helping them at all. As the \n&gt; &gt; life of a\n&gt; &gt; sannyasin=\r\n is meant only to reach the highest Reality, and as he has \n&gt; &gt; already pas=\r\nsed\n&gt; &gt; through the lower stages of spiritual evolution, he may appear to b=\r\ne \n&gt; &gt; not working\n&gt; &gt; for the rest of humanity at large; but it is to be b=\r\norne in mind that \n&gt; &gt; he exercises\n&gt; &gt; a silent and unnoticed but powerful=\r\n influence for the good of the \n&gt; &gt; public. That\n&gt; &gt; itself is the service =\r\nhe is rendering to the society and that is the \n&gt; &gt; highest and\n&gt; &gt; the mos=\r\nt beneficent service that one could ever do to man. One who is \n&gt; &gt; intent =\r\nupon\n&gt; &gt; realizing the peace, the bliss, the One Without a Second=C3=A2=E2=\r\n=82=AC&quot;Shantam, \n&gt; &gt; Shivam,\n&gt; &gt; Advaitam=C3=A2=E2=82=AC&quot;is the most powerf=\r\nul and the useful friend of the world!\n&gt; \n&gt; Correct. But, not every sannyas=\r\nin may have enough &quot;spiritual evolution&quot; \n&gt; to exert such &quot;powerful influen=\r\nce for the good of the public&quot;. The \n&gt; question here is not whether one has=\r\n renounced X, Y, Z external things \n&gt; or not. The question is whether one h=\r\nas renounced ego, doershi