ants to cling to one, because of her conditioning and \n&gt; &gt; spirit=\r\nual evolution, it is fine. She is not necessarily a bad person \n&gt; &gt; or a &quot;l=\r\neech&quot;. If one engages in dharmik and unselfish actions to make \n&gt; &gt; one&#39;s w=\r\nife happy in various ways, as far as possible, it is not bad \n&gt; &gt; and does =\r\nnot imply an undesirable attachment. If one *expects* \n&gt; &gt; something from w=\r\nife in return, THAT expectation is bad. THAT \n&gt; &gt; expectation of something =\r\nback from wife is a leech that sucks blood \n&gt; &gt; from one&#39;s soul.\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; Se=\r\neing the world, people and objects as obstructions or temptations or \n&gt; &gt; &quot;=\r\nleeches&quot; is silly. Being disgusted with the world is as much an \n&gt; &gt; attach=\r\nment (a negative attachment) as is being fascinated with it! \n&gt; &gt; World and=\r\n people can exist and act in ways that may be natural to \n&gt; &gt; them. Whateve=\r\nr they do, they are never the problem or blockage for \n&gt; &gt; your own spiritu=\r\nal evolution. You may do various actions and give \n&gt; &gt; various things to va=\r\nrious people, based on kaarmik debts, and nothing \n&gt; &gt; you do is necessaril=\r\ny a bondage. Actions never bind you, it is \n&gt; &gt; expectation of specific res=\r\nults from those actions that binds you. \n&gt; &gt; Give freely and magnanimously;=\r\n and take whatever comes back naturally, \n&gt; &gt; with no excitement and no reg=\r\nret. Remove ANY expectation that may \n&gt; &gt; exist in your mind, from ANYONE, =\r\nand become completely free. THAT is \n&gt; &gt; true sannyasa or renunciation, not=\r\n seeing people as leeches that cling \n&gt; &gt; on to you.\n&gt; &gt;\n&gt; &gt; If one becomes=\r\n a sannyasin because one is fed up with the world, it is \n&gt; &gt; probably a ba=\r\nd idea. When one discharges most of one&#39;s duties and \n&gt; &gt; responsibilities =\r\nto others, a sense of genuine renunc